The paper describes experiments with a closed-loop robotic system integrating a CNN and a Dynamic and Active Pixel Vision Sensor (DAVIS) in a predator/prey scenario. This involves machine vision systems for robotic applications, which suggests the paper belongs to the Robotics (cs.RO) sub-category. The paper also describes the use of convolutional neural networks (CNNs) for vision processing, which suggests the Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition (cs.CV) sub-category. The paper also mentions the training of the CNN offline, which suggests the Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-category. Additionally, the paper describes the use of deep learning technology, which suggests the Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE) sub-category. Finally, the paper involves the use of algorithms for recognizing the position and size of the prey robot, which suggests the Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category.
